<TITLE> Barguna Abahani keep semi hopes alive </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 15 (bdnews24.com)  Barguna Abahani Krira Chakra kept their hopes of playing in the semi-finals of the Bashundhara Club Cup Championship alive when they handed a 2-1 defeat to Sadar Upazila Krira Sangstha of Shariatpur at Cox's Bazar Stadium on Monday. Abahani raised their tally to four points from two games of Group A, three points ahead of Pabna Brothers Union. The Pabna outfit, who held Abahani to a 2-2 draw, will now face Shariatpur outfit on Wednesday to see who goes into the last four. Back to the match, Nantu put Abahani ahead in the 28th minute while Sagir made it 2-0 two minutes from time. Imam Hossain struck the lone goal for the losers in second half stoppage time. At the Shamsul Huda Stadium in Jessore, Dinajpur Football Academy refused to play just five minutes before the final whistle citing unfair play by host district's outfit Shaheed Muktijoddha Sangsad Moeen Smriti Sangsad. Tournament committee coordinator Fazlur Rahman Babul told bdnews24.com that the Dinajpur FA left the field five minutes before the final whistle after Moeen Smriti struck the decider while a Dinajpur player laid down the ground after sustaining injury. The local outfit were leading 3-2 when Dinajpur Football Academy left the field. Babul said that they were waiting for reports from match commissioner as well as referee before taking a decision. bd
